<br>
No words were exchanged as the two continued to meet metal with metal.  Both sword and scimitar able to meet in a loud and angry dance.  Never meeting flesh or armour.  As the Roman's brut strength pushed Hippolyte back, he was able to push her to the ground suddenly.  His sword tip meeting her chest he grinned above her.  Carefully, looking the amazon on the ground over.<br>
<br>
&quot;You were the one who came in and attempted to burn our village and scattered our horses,&quot; he growled.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, It was I,&quot; Hippolyte glared back.  &quot;You and your men do not belong on these lands.  They are owned by all amazons...free women. Unlike those you have taken and forced to be your wives!&quot;<br>
<br>
The man pushed his sword harder...pressing into Hippolyte's tanned skin.  &quot;There is no such thing as a free woman.&quot;  <br>
<br>
The strong man pulled his sword's tip and then reached down and grabbed Hippolyte by the arm yanking her up on her feet.  In one smooth move, he twisted her around.  His strong hands gripping her wrists together.  &quot;And now you will see that woman.&quot; <br>
<br>
Hippolyte felt her wrists were suddenly bound together. She tried to fight the large man off, but she was no match for the strength of this man who towered over her.  He laughed as <br>
slipped a cloth into her mouth and then tied it behind her head.  Making her unable to speek.  Lifting the amazon up over his shoulder, Hippolyte's booted feet began to kick hard.  The strong man wrapped an arm around her legs tightly, making it hard for Hippolyte to move.  But, she continued to fight.  <br>
<br>
With a curse, he pushed her off his shoulder.  Hippolyte's body falling to the ground hard, her head hitting a stump of a tree.  The blunt hit, caused trauma to her head...knocking Hipp out for the moment.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thank you,&quot; The roman thanked his God and then picked up the amazon once again.  This time...making it much easier to carry her back  to the village.<br>
<br>
In the distance, the sound of a horn went off.  Calling back the men to their 'village'.  Most of the trained romans suddenly dissappeared.  But, a few remained ...angry in their fighting.<br>
